RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WATER FIGHT chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the turn and kicked clear in the lane. ONE TOUGH DAME tracked the pace setter on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, challenged from the four path coming around the bend, was outkicked in the stretch and chased the winner home through the final furlong. REBEL CONSORT raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, launched a bid while saving ground around the turn and finished evenly, no match for the top two. REASONABLY LOVELY hopped up and bumped with the horse tooo her inside leaving the gate, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and improved position mildly in the stretch. NOBLE ATTITUDE veered out and brushed with the horse to her outside at the break, raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, came around the bend in the four and five path and never threatened. BEAST BUNNY bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, recovered to led the way from the rail up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the three path around the turn and tired further in the stretch. ITRIEDSELLINGHER bumped with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, trailed the field throughout, saved ground around the turn and was never a factor.

DONYA'S MAGIC hit the gate leaving it, recovered to chase the leader up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and tired in the lane.

SHUT IT CALI raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the early going, continued around the bend in the two path and was empty from there. WIFEY MATERIAL brushed with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, stalked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and tired in the stretch.

IN HONOR OF ARTIE was pinched back leaving the gate, raced in the five path around the first bend, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, began a bid from the four path coming around the second bend and improved position mildly in the stretch. KING OF CHAOS trailed the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the second turn and never threatened. SUMMER PALACE saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and showed no kick. EIGHT WEEKS LONG raced in the four path around the fist turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the two path and was empty in the lane. MIDNIGHT TEQUILA raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, saved ground around the far turn and made no bid.
